# 🖱️ Virtual Mouse Using Hand Gesture Control

This project is a **Virtual Mouse** that lets you control your computer cursor using hand gestures via a webcam. Built using **Python**, **OpenCV**, **MediaPipe**, and **PyAutoGUI**, it enables real-time gesture tracking for actions like cursor movement, clicking, and more — hands-free!


## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Python**
- **OpenCV** – for video capture and image processing
- **MediaPipe** – for hand landmark detection
- **PyAutoGUI** – for controlling the mouse and screen interactions
- **Numpy** – for calculations and coordinate mapping

## 🚀 Features

- Move mouse cursor using your index finger
- Click with gesture (e.g., thumb and index finger together)
- Scroll gesture (optional extension)
- Real-time performance with webcam
- Adjustable frame reduction and smoothing for better UX



